        "nav-contact": "Contact",
        "bio-title": "About Me",
        "bio-text": "I've been building things for the web since 1999. What started as curiosity at 14 became a career that's gone through web design, data analysis, UX, and product leadership — always in environments where the product has to earn trust rather than assume it. For 14 years I've led product at INAES, a national regulatory institution in Argentina managing 22,000+ organizations. I own the roadmap, drive discovery, align stakeholders across legal, operations and engineering, and ship. Most recently I proposed and am co-leading an AI transformation program that's bringing automation in-house across 20 operational areas — including fine-tuning an LLM on regulated financial documentation. Outside of that, I founded NDZ Labs, a Product Intelligence Company where I research, design and validate modular operational systems for underserved markets. The model runs on AI agents that compress execution cycles across design, development and operations. I focus on the strategy, the architecture, and the problems worth solving. My work follows a consistent pattern: I find processes that force people to depend on others and turn them into systems where they can operate on their own.",
        "bio-text-1": "I've been building things for the web since 1999.",
